Master Answer:
It is not too late for your child to get immunized. We recommend that you contact your local health unit to make an appointment.  A public health nurse will review the recommended vaccines and schedule with you, answer your questions, and provide the vaccines. You can find the contact information for your local health unit here.  
You can find tips for a positive immunization experience here.
